Comment: 0,0:00:01.00,0:00:03.57,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}英文字幕
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.00,0:00:03.57,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- Behind me is a Falcon 9 rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.97,0:00:06.92,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now, with these things taking off every two weeks or so--
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.77,0:00:09.54,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- --taking payloads to the International Space Station,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.60,0:00:11.64,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}maybe putting a satellite up into orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.71,0:00:13.38,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or perhaps even a car,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.44,0:00:17.24,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it's pretty easy to forget just how revolutionary this rocket really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.88,0:00:19.61,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But why is it so cool?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.68,0:00:21.72,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Well, it's not just its awesome name.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.31,0:00:25.93,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's also the fact that this rocket can actually land.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.68,0:00:32.70,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Let's take a moment to appreciate just how mind-blowingly awesome this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.68,0:00:38.58,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Okay, so how on earth do Falcon 9 rockets land?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.96,0:00:41.16,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}What are the mechanics?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.78,0:00:42.74,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The physics?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.31,0:00:44.40,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}How does it do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.64,0:00:53.21,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}On this episode, we're going to go to SpaceX to see the first rocket to ever land,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.65,0:00:58.92,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Dude! This is not a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.21,0:01:01.34,1080P-shsm-60,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\an8\fs50\fn思源黑体 Bold}--and fly like a Falcon 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.49,0:01:06.23,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm going to use a grid fin to steer like a SpaceX rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.93,0:01:11.37,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I mean, what could go wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.73,0:01:18.21,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}TIM: Ever since I was little, I've been obsessed with space.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.52,0:01:23.01,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm Tim Dodd, but most people know me as the Everyday Astronaut.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.31,0:01:27.05,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}A couple years ago, I bought a spacesuit just for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.37,0:01:30.36,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I had no idea where that would take me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.85,0:01:34.09,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Woo!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.16,0:01:39.02,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now I'm a mission to get everyone to nerd out on space.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.24,0:01:50.21,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- MALE REPORTER: In preparation for her maiden voyage--
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.68,0:01:55.57,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- TIM: The space shuttle program was NASA's first crack at reusable spacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.81,0:01:56.70,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Unfortunately,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.93,0:02:02.92,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}thanks to design compromises and the need to refurbish key components with each and every launch,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.98,0:02:09.29,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}flying and re-flying the reusable space shuttles turned out to be really expensive,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.36,0:02:14.32,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}with the program costing a total of $209 billion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.83,0:02:17.27,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- TIM: That's billion with a B.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.53,0:02:20.14,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So, NASA grounded the space shuttle program.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.67,0:02:27.23,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Then, along came Space Exploration Technologies, better known as SpaceX.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.04,0:02:30.75,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- WOMAN: We have liftoff. Falcon has cleared the tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.88,0:02:37.95,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- In 2011, when Elon Musk announced plans for his "little" rocket company to try to reuse rockets,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.41,0:02:40.05,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}most people were pretty skeptical.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.38,0:02:41.44,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Then they actually did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.78,0:02:46.96,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This is that actual rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.20,0:02:51.04,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}On December 21, 2015, this thing took off on Cape Canaveral,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.28,0:02:54.63,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}went up into space, and a few minutes later, came back down to Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.84,0:03:00.28,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}marking the first time in human history an orbital-class liquid rocket booster landed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.53,0:03:06.03,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Landing a rocket, of course, means you should be able to reuse the rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.65,0:03:10.52,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And that is what makes the Falcon 9 so groundbreaking--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.38,0:03:14.01,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- TIM: --the fact that you can cost-effectively fly them--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.06,0:03:18.51,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- TIM: --land them, then fly them over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.45,0:03:26.83,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- TIM: To help us understand just how insanely difficult landing a rocket is,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.19,0:03:32.73,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm not gonna lie, this is probably the weirdest start to an interview ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.75,0:03:33.80,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But here's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.17,0:03:39.41,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Ever since I learned who Joe Barnard is, I've wanted to see his Falcon Heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.65,0:03:42.33,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}He's the king of model rockets.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.69,0:03:43.81,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Joe, how are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.10,0:03:44.77,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- What up, Tim?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.00,0:03:47.05,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- Uh...I should probably turn around now, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.24,0:03:49.04,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- I think we're--I think we're go for turnaround.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.28,0:03:49.99,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.60,0:03:52.33,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.39,0:03:57.04,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Oh my gosh, dude! This is not a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.13,0:03:58.55,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}How big is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.57,0:04:00.05,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- JOE: It's a little over a meter tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.26,0:04:02.40,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- I didn't know this thing was over a meter tall!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.76,0:04:04.88,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Or 3.3 feet tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.91,0:04:06.21,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- No, we use metric in aerospace.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.53,0:04:10.88,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- TIM: Joe is working on getting his 1:48 scale model rocket to land,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.28,0:04:12.78,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}just like the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.10,0:04:15.88,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- You know, I can afford to build this scale of rockets.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.93,0:04:19.39,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I just try to make them as complex as possible in the way that the real thing works.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.73,0:04:24.72,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- TIM: Okay, so there's a lot of complex rocket science that goes into landing a rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.78,0:04:26.10,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- JOE: Something called thrust vectoring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.16,0:04:30.75,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And they both get gimbaled at the same time if you're within a certain range of your apogee.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.82,0:04:36.01,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And as I'm sure you know, the Falcon 9 uses something called Guidance For Fuel Optimal Landing Divert.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.22,0:04:40.01,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's actually a pretty simple thing called a third order polynomial.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.30,0:04:43.08,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- So, this one has a Tesla on the top?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.13,0:04:44.90,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- JOE: Not right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.92,0:04:47.19,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But I'm thinking we should put a Hot Wheels in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.95,0:04:50.75,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- TIM: Now, for those of you who don't speak rocket,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.17,0:04:52.97,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}let me translate what Joe's saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.63,0:04:55.62,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This is how a Falcon 9 lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.90,0:04:59.72,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}After stage separation, the hypersonic grid fins deploy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.40,0:05:04.13,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Then, cold gas thrusters fire up to reorient the rocket for re-entry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.67,0:05:06.13,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They're those white flashes you're seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.64,0:05:11.52,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Three of the rocket's Merlin engines fire up to slow the rocket down as it re-enters the Earth's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.98,0:05:16.35,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Then, the grid fins do their thing to precisely steer the rocket towards the landing pad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.96,0:05:19.51,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Another engine fires up, and the landing legs come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.82,0:05:20.73,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Touchdown!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.54,0:05:24.79,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}See, I actually know a thing or two about rocket science.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.55,0:05:32.84,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- Clearly there's a lot that goes into landing rockets.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.15,0:05:35.65,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But how hard can it really be?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.43,0:05:39.23,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Well, today, I'm determined to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.60,0:05:43.71,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm going to fly and then land just like a Falcon 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.01,0:05:46.87,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And although I don't have any Merlin engines...yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.94,0:05:50.31,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I've got the next best thing-- a vertical wind tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.85,0:05:55.78,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Here to help me fly like a Falcon is science junkie Olivia Pavco Giaccia.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.45,0:06:03.96,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- Realistically, how bad could we get hurt doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.00,0:06:06.97,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- Potentially anything you've seen on a football field I've seen in the tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.10,0:06:08.32,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- So, like concussions?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.36,0:06:09.86,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- I've been knocked out twice in the tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.10,0:06:11.37,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- TIM: Wait, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.53,0:06:14.34,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'd better take this safety briefing seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.46,0:06:16.40,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- INSTRUCTOR: So we're gonna go over a few safety procedures.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.45,0:06:18.44,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The really important thing to remember is symmetry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.70,0:06:19.57,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- TIM: Symmetry?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.78,0:06:22.28,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Like the grid fins' X-wing configuration.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.30,0:06:24.78,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Oh, I love that they made "Star Wars" a real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.90,0:06:26.88,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Ooh, when's the next one coming out?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.28,0:06:28.68,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I really liked that last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.78,0:06:30.62,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Wait, I think this guy's almost finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.93,0:06:33.29,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Uh, ask a follow-up just so he thinks you're paying attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.22,0:06:35.66,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So how long have you been doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.72,0:06:39.18,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- Um, I've been working here, uh, on and off for 12 years now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.20,0:06:40.85,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- You're pretty good in there? - Pretty decent, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.12,0:06:42.73,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- TIM: What are the odds that on day one,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.82,0:06:46.42,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I outdo you with all these cool flips that I've been working on in my dreams?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.53,0:06:47.69,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- Astronomically slim.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.73,0:06:48.82,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- Mm. Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.84,0:06:51.14,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- TIM: I'll take those odds.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.92,0:06:56.13,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now, you may not know this, and I may not look like it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.33,0:06:57.97,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but I'm a natural athlete.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.72,0:07:02.58,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And I've got a feeling that flying in a wind tunnel will be a breeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.33,0:07:07.20,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Obviously, before we land like a Falcon 9,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.83,0:07:09.77,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}we first have to fly like one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.48,0:07:16.99,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}All the air being generated by the giant fan is pushing us up hard enough to beat gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.95,0:07:21.50,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now, our instructor is pulling and moving us around the wind tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.62,0:07:27.44,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But we can also manipulate the air pushing us up by making small adjustments to our bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.69,0:07:34.81,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Small, teeny-tiny movements to our arms, legs, and torso alter the direction of lift and allow us to steer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.48,0:07:37.62,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Considering this is our first flight,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.93,0:07:40.24,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'd say Olivia and I are doing pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.13,0:07:42.82,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}That was freaking awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.05,0:07:45.13,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And as you can tell, I'm really good at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.32,0:07:47.77,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But the whole point of this is for science.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.96,0:07:49.97,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}We're trying to figure out how to land a rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.60,0:07:55.54,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}To really experience what it's like to land a rocket,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.85,0:07:59.07,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I brought my human-sized, garage-engineered grid fin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.43,0:08:02.93,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And like a Falcon 9, I'm gonna use it to steer me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.77,0:08:04.95,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- Help me understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.21,0:08:08.26,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}What is it that makes grid fins better than regular fins?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.35,0:08:12.52,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- TIM: The big thing about a grid fin is that it can be deployed as it comes back down into the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.59,0:08:13.56,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}All of a sudden, you have wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.64,0:08:15.47,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}'Cause on the way up, you don't really want wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.18,0:08:19.62,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- And what is it about the grid fins' grid formation?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.68,0:08:22.36,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- TIM: There are, basically, hundreds of little wings tucked in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.43,0:08:23.87,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's a way to be compact.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.14,0:08:25.75,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}You also can apply a lot of torque,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.76,0:08:28.64,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but not a lot of movement that needs to happen to turn and rotate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.72,0:08:34.06,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Even at idle speeds, the wind is really, really strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.18,0:08:36.28,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}How fast is it the wind going right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.46,0:08:38.85,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- Our idle speed is 900 RPMs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.96,0:08:43.45,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Our reach speed tops out at 2,100 RPMs-- about 110 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.52,0:08:49.21,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- Even at this slow speed, that has a lot of effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.40,0:08:53.23,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Okay, things are about to get real.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.65,0:09:14.83,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This is not a SpaceX-approved explanation of their technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.64,0:09:23.76,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But in order to complete my Falcon transformation,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.05,0:09:25.03,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I've gotta launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.24,0:09:28.65,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I need to blast off, and then use my grid fin to elegantly
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.83,0:09:33.23,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and accurately steer myself from the tunnel by manipulating my direction of lift.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.52,0:09:34.74,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Ready? Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.98,0:09:37.62,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In three, two, one...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.46,0:09:43.68,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And we have liftoff.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.29,0:09:47.48,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm flying like a Falcon 9...sorta.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.61,0:09:51.59,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm not really getting up as high as I thought I would.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.98,0:09:54.16,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Just trying to hang on to this grid fin,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.37,0:09:56.26,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it's a lot harder than it looks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.77,0:10:03.20,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Every tiny bit of movement I make creates a lot of torque thanks to the grids on my grid fin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.26,0:10:08.55,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's really hard to hang on, much less steer with this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.47,0:10:17.95,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Fun fact: it took SpaceX more than five years and several failed attempts to land their first Falcon 9 rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.40,0:10:21.13,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Yeah, that's a lot of fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.66,0:10:23.57,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So, I guess I'm in good company.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.48,0:10:28.19,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Well, our instructor wants to give it a go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.56,0:10:29.46,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Hmph, good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.57,0:10:35.00,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- TIM: Whoa, this guy is good!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.25,0:10:39.34,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Our mild-mannered wind tunnel instructor's flying around like Superman.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.08,0:10:44.98,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}He's turning himself by making small adjustments to the grid fin's angle and redirecting lift,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.10,0:10:46.84,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}just like a Falcon 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.48,0:10:50.48,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Yes, yes! Our grid fin works!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.16,0:10:56.45,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Well, we learned the hard way that landing rockets is super difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.28,0:11:02.99,1080P-shsm-60,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\an8\fs50\fn思源黑体 Bold}So, here's to all those genius rocket scientists that make it look easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.05,0:11:07.96,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm Tim Dodd, the Everyday Astronaut,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.03,0:11:09.82,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}bringing space down to Earth for everyday people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.27,0:11:13.30,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}For more out-of-this-world content,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.60,0:11:16.18,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}be sure and follow us on Facebook Watch.
